    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-05-21T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-05-21T22:00:00-05:00" n="188"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d188">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.51/243: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Tuck</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-21T23:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 21, 1942—11 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>336. Your 727, May 18, 4 p.m., section 5,<note n="79" xml:id="d188fn79">Last two
                        paragraphs of telegram.</note> per first paragraph. In reply to a question
                    at press conference today, the Secretary of State answered: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“We have had up fully and freely the question of our deep concern for the
                            French people in their distress and in their conquered situation and our
                            great desire to see restoration of all of her popular institutions, all
                            of those rights and benefits and blessings that the great French
                            Republic once enjoyed.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
